<b>Her and him?</b>

223
00:16:29,289 --> 00:16:30,373
<b>Are you insane?</b>

224
00:16:30,624 --> 00:16:33,460
<b>I'm your lawyer: It's that
or a nasty divorce.</b>

225
00:16:33,960 --> 00:16:35,879
<b>She'll never agree to it!</b>

226
00:16:36,297 --> 00:16:39,383
<b>Put 2 million Euros
in her account, and she will.</b>

227
00:16:39,634 --> 00:16:41,969
<b>She's well-paid
and not out for money!</b>

228
00:16:42,720 --> 00:16:45,848
<b>Honest women are rare
in billionaire circles.</b>

229
00:16:46,557 --> 00:16:49,310
<b>Yes, almost as rare
as honest lawyers!</b>

230
00:16:49,811 --> 00:16:52,021
<b>Your wife must be after this guy.</b>

231
00:16:52,313 --> 00:16:54,106
<b>The girl's gotta help us.</b>

232
00:17:05,285 --> 00:17:05,953
<b>Here she is.</b>

233
00:17:33,899 --> 00:17:35,775
<b>How will he get out of it?</b>

234
00:17:36,694 --> 00:17:41,072
<b>For 2 years you swore you'd divorce,
now I must help you avoid it?</b>

235
00:17:41,322 --> 00:17:43,909
<b>I'm in deep shit.
Only you can help me.</b>

236
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,953
<b>Right, to keep your wife.</b>

237
00:17:46,203 --> 00:17:47,997
<b>And go live with a stranger.</b>

238
00:17:49,415 --> 00:17:53,085
<b>My wife's a majority shareholder
in the companies I run.</b>

239
00:17:53,420 --> 00:17:54,963
<b>Damn that, I want one thing.</b>

240
00:17:55,213 --> 00:17:56,256
<b>What?</b>

241
00:17:56,672 --> 00:17:58,507
<b>A good reason
to accept this absurdity.</b>

242
00:17:58,757 --> 00:18:00,302
<b>Loving me a little is one.</b>

243
00:18:00,885 --> 00:18:03,262
<b>Can you think of any others?</b>

244
00:18:03,512 --> 00:18:05,265
<b>I need a month to neutralize her.</b>

245
00:18:05,474 --> 00:18:08,602
<b>With some financial maneuvers
that'll get me out of this.</b>

246
00:18:08,810 --> 00:18:11,813
<b>In a month I'll divorce:
We'll start a new life!</b>

247
00:18:12,397 --> 00:18:13,524
<b>I trust you.</b>

248
00:18:14,107 --> 00:18:16,318
<b>I knew I could count on you, darling!</b>

249
00:18:17,861 --> 00:18:20,989
<b>Not so fast.
I'll show you how much I trust you.</b>

250
00:18:21,239 --> 00:18:23,284
<b>Put 10 million Euros
in a bank for me</b>

251
00:18:23,493 --> 00:18:24,869
<b>in a tax-haven.</b>

252
00:18:25,536 --> 00:18:26,412
<b>10 million?</b>

253
00:18:28,206 --> 00:18:29,917
<b>No, 20 million.</b>

254
00:18:30,167 --> 00:18:32,503
<b>It takes a big sum to make this fun.</b>

255
00:18:32,752 --> 00:18:36,757
<b>I told my lawyer you weren't
after money. Sorry I was wrong.</b>

256
00:18:37,007 --> 00:18:38,592
<b>You weren't. It's a deposit.</b>

257
00:18:38,842 --> 00:18:40,928
<b>Divorce in a month, you get it all back.</b>

258
00:18:41,178 --> 00:18:45,474
<b>If you don't,
I'll consider I got paid for a job.</b>

259
00:18:45,724 --> 00:18:47,351
<b>20 million? That's insane!</b>

260
00:18:47,894 --> 00:18:51,104
<b>It's nothing,
if you're so sure you'll divorce.</b>

261
00:19:08,289 --> 00:19:09,499
<b>Thanks.</b>

262
00:19:16,423 --> 00:19:17,466
<b>I'll park it, sir.</b>

263
00:19:18,591 --> 00:19:20,594
<b>Drive, I have to talk to you.</b>

264
00:19:27,393 --> 00:19:30,312
<b>- There's our lot.
- Go ahead, park.</b>

265
00:19:41,032 --> 00:19:43,827
<b>- You're Francois Pignon?
- That's right.</b>

266
00:19:44,493 --> 00:19:47,414
<b>I'm a lawyer with a client
who needs your help.</b>

267
00:19:48,123 --> 00:19:48,874
<b>My help?</b>

268
00:19:49,624 --> 00:19:52,544
<b>All this must stay
strictly confidential.</b>

269
00:19:53,211 --> 00:19:56,423
<b>You must put a woman up
at your place for a while.</b>

270
00:19:57,007 --> 00:19:57,757
<b>A woman?</b>

271
00:19:58,008 --> 00:19:59,885
<b>Yes, and pretend to be a couple.</b>

272
00:20:01,596 --> 00:20:03,139
<b>Sorry, I don't quite follow you.</b>

273
00:20:03,389 --> 00:20:05,641
<b>It's simple.
A woman will live with you:</b>

274
00:20:05,892 --> 00:20:07,768
<b>People must think
she's your girlfriend.</b>

275
00:20:09,645 --> 00:20:10,438
<b>Who is she?</b>

276
00:20:10,771 --> 00:20:14,276
<b>She's a... how can I put it?
Let's say a supermodel.</b>

277
00:20:14,526 --> 00:20:15,569
<b>- A supermodel?
- Right...</b>

278
00:20:15,819 --> 00:20:18,197
<b>Quite well known... very well known.</b>

279
00:20:18,571 --> 00:20:21,033
<b>- Who'll live with me?
- For a few days.</b>

280
00:20:21,782 --> 00:20:22,993
<b>How much must I pay?</b>

281
00:20:23,494 --> 00:20:24,745
<b>No, we pay you.</b>

282
00:20:25,162 --> 00:20:26,997
<b>To live with a supermodel?</b>

283
00:20:27,247 --> 00:20:28,916
<b>Name your price.</b>

284
00:20:31,293 --> 00:20:32,295
<b>You're putting me on?</b>

285
00:20:32,836 --> 00:20:34,463
<b>No, it's a serious matter.</b>

286
00:20:36,298 --> 00:20:37,674
<b>Where's the camera?</b>

287
00:20:38,009 --> 00:20:39,093
<b>What?</b>

288
00:20:39,344 --> 00:20:41,053
<b>The camera, where is it?</b>

289
00:20:42,305 --> 00:20:45,099
<b>You sure had me going.
You got me!</b>

290
00:20:45,517 --> 00:20:46,351
<b>And I...</b>

291
00:20:46,810 --> 00:20:51,565
<b>Mr Pignon, this is very serious
and very urgent.</b>

292
00:20:52,650 --> 00:20:53,274
<b>Well?</b>

293
00:20:53,983 --> 00:20:56,110
<b>He agreed.
He didn't get it, but agreed.</b>

294
00:20:56,361 --> 00:20:59,030
<b>- How much does he want?
- 32,450 Euros.</b>

295
00:21:00,574 --> 00:21:02,827
<b>The exactness of the sum
surprised me, too.</b>

296
00:21:03,077 --> 00:21:06,288
<b>32,450 Euros.
Not a penny more or less!</b>

297
00:21:06,539 --> 00:21:08,123
<b>How did she react?</b>

298
00:21:12,671 --> 00:21:13,713
<b>She'll cost more.</b>

299
00:21:14,129 --> 00:21:14,840
<b>How much?</b>

300
00:21:15,799 --> 00:21:17,007
<b>...million Euros.</b>

301
00:21:17,926 --> 00:21:18,510
<b>What?</b>

302
00:21:19,010 --> 00:21:20,678
<b>20 million Euros!</b>

303
00:21:23,223 --> 00:21:24,558
<b>- Is this a joke?
- Not at all.</b>

304
00:21:24,808 --> 00:21:27,185
<b>I swore I'd divorce:
She didn't believe me.</b>

305
00:21:27,811 --> 00:21:28,979
<b>I can see why.</b>

306
00:21:29,521 --> 00:21:30,480
<b>Spare me your quips.</b>

307
00:21:31,439 --> 00:21:33,733
<b>Sorry.
You said she wasn't after money.</b>

308
00:21:33,984 --> 00:21:36,570
<b>It's a deposit.
I get it back when I divorce.</b>

309
00:21:37,488 --> 00:21:38,947
<b>That's blackmail.</b>

310
00:21:43,995 --> 00:21:46,998
<b>I love her,
and I'm completely cornered.</b>

311
00:22:03,724 --> 00:22:05,017
<b>- Mr Pignon?
- Yes.</b>

312
00:22:05,309 --> 00:22:06,810
<b>I'm Christine Levasseur.</b>

313
00:22:07,019 --> 00:22:09,980
<b>May I ask you a few questions?
Can I come in?</b>

314
00:22:10,230 --> 00:22:10,814
<b>Please do.</b>

315
00:22:17,405 --> 00:22:19,156
<b>You seen this picture?</b>

316
00:22:19,449 --> 00:22:20,575
<b>Was that the door, hon?</b>

317
00:22:22,619 --> 00:22:23,495
<b>Ma'am.</b>

318
00:22:50,481 --> 00:22:51,148
<b>Hello?</b>

319
00:22:51,398 --> 00:22:52,859
<b><i>They beat you to it.</b></i>

320
00:22:53,109 --> 00:22:56,695
<b>I couldn't be faster.
I found him in 24-hours.</b>

321
00:22:56,946 --> 00:22:58,739
<b>I just left his place: She was there.</b>

322
00:22:58,989 --> 00:23:00,366
<b>Maybe they are an item.</b>

323
00:23:03,244 --> 00:23:05,664
<b>We can't rule it out completely.</b>

324
00:23:05,997 --> 00:23:09,626
<b>Watch them day and night.
We'll soon find out.</b>

325
00:23:20,638 --> 00:23:21,347
<b>Hello?</b>

326
00:23:21,681 --> 00:23:23,975
<b>She's hired Berman.
Ex-cop, now private.</b>

327
00:23:24,183 --> 00:23:26,060
<b><i>The green Renault behind you.</b></i>

328
00:23:27,520 --> 00:23:29,856
<b>Take Baume Avenue
and park by number 42.</b>

329
00:23:41,033 --> 00:23:43,370
<b><i>A car's waiting for you in the yard.</b></i>

330
00:23:43,787 --> 00:23:44,663
<b>A black Audi.</b>

331
00:23:50,836 --> 00:23:54,298
<b>Take the back exit
into a street behind the building.</b>

332
00:24:32,255 --> 00:24:34,423
<b>It's a friend's house,
you'll be fine here.</b>

333
00:24:34,673 --> 00:24:35,884
<b>Sit down.</b>

334
00:24:36,718 --> 00:24:40,430
<b>The bank data: You have
20 million Euros in this account.</b>

335
00:24:42,140 --> 00:24:44,434
<b>Admit that it's a tidy sum.</b>

336
00:24:44,684 --> 00:24:47,687
<b>Less than the cost of a divorce.
Ten times less?</b>

337
00:24:48,855 --> 00:24:51,191
<b>I'll need a signature.</b>

338
00:24:51,942 --> 00:24:54,110
<b>So he gets the money back
if he divorces.</b>

339
00:24:58,490 --> 00:24:59,450
<b>Love is beautiful!</b>

340
00:25:02,495 --> 00:25:04,538
<b>Let's recap...</b>

341
00:25:06,916 --> 00:25:09,210
<b>Be seen everywhere with this man:</b>

342
00:25:09,460 --> 00:25:13,005
<b>Convince those watching you
that you're a real couple.</b>

343
00:25:14,423 --> 00:25:15,424
<b>Yes?</b>

344
00:25:16,677 --> 00:25:18,052
<b>Right away.</b>

345
00:25:18,803 --> 00:25:19,972
<b>He's here.</b>

346
00:25:20,972 --> 00:25:21,932
<b>I'll leave you.</b>

347
00:25:27,437 --> 00:25:29,398
<b>Sorry, darling. I'm a bit late.</b>

348
00:25:29,648 --> 00:25:31,442
<b>I'm so happy to see you.</b>

349
00:25:32,734 --> 00:25:34,528
<b>It's all done,
money's been transferred.</b>

350
00:25:34,778 --> 00:25:37,282
<b>An accounting headache,
but I'll skip that.</b>

351
00:25:37,490 --> 00:25:40,742
<b>Let's chitchat.
How's the divorce coming along?</b>

352
00:25:42,119 --> 00:25:44,789
<b>Elena, be nice to me.
Things aren't easy.</b>

353
00:25:45,039 --> 00:25:46,624
<b>Because of your wife?</b>

354
00:25:47,250 --> 00:25:49,002
<b>No, because of you.</b>

355
00:25:49,252 --> 00:25:51,880
<b>I feel guilty
about what you're going through.</b>

356
00:25:52,130 --> 00:25:56,134
<b>Living with that pathetic guy
must be dreadful.</b>

357
00:25:56,968 --> 00:25:59,053
<b>Not really. In fact, it's quite fun.</b>

358
00:25:59,345 --> 00:26:02,308
<b>The apartment is barely livable,
but the guy is cute.</b>

359
00:26:02,558 --> 00:26:05,352
<b>Cute? Are we talking
about the same guy?</b>

360
00:26:05,769 --> 00:26:07,897
<b>He has lovely eyes,
and he makes me laugh.</b>

361
00:26:08,397 --> 00:26:11,483
<b>It's sweet of you
to try and reassure me,</b>

362
00:26:11,734 --> 00:26:14,821
<b>but it's hard on you.
Thank you for playing along.</b>

363
00:26:15,030 --> 00:26:17,657
<b>You know me.
I can't be with two men at once.</b>

364
00:26:17,908 --> 00:26:18,658
<b>That's not funny.</b>

365
00:26:18,908 --> 00:26:21,828
<b>You made me live with another man.
I do my best.</b>

366
00:26:22,078 --> 00:26:24,039
<b>Cooking, the dishes, the laundry...</b>

367
00:26:24,331 --> 00:26:24,998
<b>Not funny!</b>

368
00:26:25,332 --> 00:26:27,542
<b>Your lawyer said
we must be seen together,</b>

369
00:26:27,792 --> 00:26:30,545
<b>and look like a real couple.</b>

370
00:26:30,837 --> 00:26:33,465
<b>I love you.
Soon we'll be together forever.</b>

371
00:26:33,965 --> 00:26:37,470
<b>Gotta go. I can't keep him waiting,
we have a lunch date.</b>

372
00:26:46,229 --> 00:26:49,106
<b>Don't sulk.
I kicked you out because I was low.</b>

373
00:26:49,315 --> 00:26:51,527
<b>Miss me?
See, you're alone like a dog!</b>

374
00:26:51,901 --> 00:26:52,985
<b>I'm not alone.</b>

375
00:26:53,236 --> 00:26:56,740
<b>Sure! The neighbors complain
of your all night parties,</b>

376
00:26:56,989 --> 00:26:59,283
<b>and chicks shrieking in ecstasy.</b>

377
00:27:05,165 --> 00:27:08,209
<b>Don't park it, I'll be fast.
Is Francois here?</b>

378
00:27:09,753 --> 00:27:10,504
<b>Francois?</b>

379
00:27:30,108 --> 00:27:31,359
<b>Hi, honey!</b>

380
00:27:33,779 --> 00:27:35,029
<b>Is our lunch on?</b>

381
00:27:35,406 --> 00:27:37,365
<b>No, I'm busy, stop by later.</b>

382
00:27:51,714 --> 00:27:53,424
<b>Thanks. Bye.</b>

383
00:28:02,975 --> 00:28:04,144
<b>Bye...</b>

384
00:28:10,442 --> 00:28:12,485
<b>- Friend of yours?
- Yeah.</b>

385
00:28:17,658 --> 00:28:19,326
<b>Known her long?</b>

386
00:28:19,535 --> 00:28:21,662
<b>No. We're living together.</b>

387
00:28:23,998 --> 00:28:26,083
<b>- There were photographers.
- Really?</b>

388
00:28:26,334 --> 00:28:28,461
<b>That's why I kissed you.</b>

389
00:28:29,879 --> 00:28:30,838
<b>What's so funny?</b>

390
00:28:31,088 --> 00:28:32,965
<b>The other valet, you killed him!</b>

391
00:28:33,216 --> 00:28:33,758
<b>Why?</b>

392
00:28:34,008 --> 00:28:35,928
<b>He says I'm hopeless with women.</b>

393
00:28:36,178 --> 00:28:38,346
<b>Why would he say that? He's crazy!</b>

394
00:28:38,555 --> 00:28:41,057
<b>He doesn't believe
in my powers of seduction.</b>

395
00:28:41,350 --> 00:28:42,726
<b>I don't either.</b>

396
00:28:45,728 --> 00:28:47,189
<b>Where do you usually lunch?</b>

397
00:28:47,397 --> 00:28:49,066
<b>At Luigi's, an Italian place.</b>

398
00:28:49,358 --> 00:28:52,320
<b>- I keep going straight?
- No, not Luigi's. Elsewhere.</b>

399
00:28:52,570 --> 00:28:55,072
<b>If you're a regular,
let's be seen there.</b>

400
00:28:55,322 --> 00:28:58,368
<b>Not at Luigi's. There's other places.</b>

401
00:29:00,327 --> 00:29:00,995
<b>Is it good?</b>

402
00:29:01,579 --> 00:29:02,872
<b>You read it, Mr Herve.</b>

403
00:29:03,081 --> 00:29:04,790
<b>I did?</b>

404
00:29:05,083 --> 00:29:08,086
<b>You bought it last month
and read it in one go!</b>

405
00:29:08,753 --> 00:29:12,298
<b>I don't recall it!
Yet I still have all my marbles.</b>

406
00:29:12,507 --> 00:29:15,385
<b>Then... give me a lamb chop.</b>

407
00:29:16,887 --> 00:29:20,015
<b>The butcher's next door,
this is the bookstore.</b>

408
00:29:24,352 --> 00:29:25,937
<b>This way, Mr Herve.</b>

409
00:29:28,566 --> 00:29:30,526
<b>You could've sold it to him twice.</b>

410
00:29:34,865 --> 00:29:35,657
<b>It's not him.</b>

411
00:29:35,907 --> 00:29:38,034
<b>- He won't come back.
- Just as well!</b>

412
00:29:38,577 --> 00:29:40,162
<b>I had a voice mail from him.</b>

413
00:29:40,412 --> 00:29:42,414
<b>Said he had funds
to cover my debt.</b>

414
00:29:43,039 --> 00:29:43,790
<b>Nonsense.</b>

415
00:29:44,624 --> 00:29:46,084
<b>- I didn't call back.
- Good.</b>

416
00:29:46,334 --> 00:29:49,713
<b>He's bluffing.
He can't find that kind of money!</b>

417
00:29:56,012 --> 00:29:57,470
<b>Isn't that amazing?</b>

418
00:29:57,721 --> 00:30:00,766
<b>You can pick another ring tone.
It has 40! For you!</b>

419
00:30:01,184 --> 00:30:02,894
<b>That's sweet, but I can't accept.</b>

420
00:30:03,144 --> 00:30:05,146
<b>Yes, you can!
Look how cool this one is.</b>

421
00:30:05,396 --> 00:30:07,857
<b>- How many functions?
- 100! One's for scuba diving!</b>

422
00:30:08,107 --> 00:30:08,608
<b>Wow!</b>

423
00:30:08,858 --> 00:30:10,902
<b>It's yours. Have lunch with me!</b>

424
00:30:14,740 --> 00:30:15,948
<b>OK, but a quick one.</b>

425
00:30:16,240 --> 00:30:18,284
<b>We'll be at Luigi's. I'll be back soon.</b>

426
00:30:18,911 --> 00:30:22,331
<b>No, not Luigi's. Let's go elsewhere.</b>

427
00:30:27,752 --> 00:30:30,881
<b>She's amazing.
Takes guts to kiss a guy like that.</b>

428
00:30:31,131 --> 00:30:33,425
<b>- Yes, she's giving it her all.
- Fuck you!</b>

429
00:30:33,675 --> 00:30:36,470
<b>- Beg your pardon?
- Nothing, I'm sorry.</b>

430
00:30:37,222 --> 00:30:38,180
<b>Yes?</b>

431
00:30:39,057 --> 00:30:42,185
<b>- Don't forget the meeting in Lille.
- Right, Lille.</b>

432
00:30:42,435 --> 00:30:45,855
<b>Being booed by 800 striking workers.
Just what I need!</b>

433
00:30:46,105 --> 00:30:47,857
<b>- When do I leave?
- Helicopter's ready, sir.</b>

434
00:30:48,483 --> 00:30:49,234
<b>I'm off.</b>

435
00:30:49,484 --> 00:30:52,237
<b>Watch them day and night.
Got that?</b>

436
00:30:59,912 --> 00:31:01,412
<b>Everybody's watching us!</b>

437
00:31:01,997 --> 00:31:03,957
<b>Why would you be with me?</b>

438
00:31:04,208 --> 00:31:06,836
<b>Let's up the ante:
Put your arm around me.</b>

439
00:31:07,044 --> 00:31:08,796
<b>I'll rest my head on your shoulder.</b>

440
00:31:09,004 --> 00:31:10,172
<b>Don't, they'll lynch me!</b>

441
00:31:10,422 --> 00:31:11,841
<b>Put down your fork.</b>

442
00:31:13,509 --> 00:31:14,718
<b>See the green Renault?</b>

